---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import ContactSection from "../components/ContactSection.astro";
import { CONTACT, SHOW_RESUME } from "../lib/site";
---

<Layout
  title="About"
  description="From ten years in broadcast television to full stack engineering: what I've built and what I'm looking for."
>
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 py-16 sm:py-20">
    <div class="max-w-3xl">
      <h1 class="font-display text-4xl font-semibold text-paper sm:text-5xl">
        About
      </h1>

      <div class="case-body mt-10">
        <p>
          I spent close to ten years in broadcast television before I wrote a
          line of production code, as a camera assistant and then operator.
          That background is part of why I care about shipping things that
          actually work under real conditions, not just in a demo.
        </p>

        <h2>What I've built</h2>
        <p>
          In my previous role, I built and shipped a range of production
          systems, including:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            A multi-tenant registration and licensing platform for a
            motorsport governing body, with role-based access and a
            configurable payments fee engine.
          </li>
          <li>
            A ticketing and point-of-sale platform running across multiple
            live venues, with Stripe, digital wallet, and dedicated card
            terminal integration, including allocated seating for large
            venues.
          </li>
          <li>
            A booking and subscription app for a gym, handling class bookings
            and recurring memberships.
          </li>
          <li>
            A tablet-based system for an education centre, migrated off an
            unsupported legacy stack onto one a full team could maintain.
          </li>
          <li>
            Platform and database migrations across hosting providers, with
            measurable cost savings.
          </li>
          <li>
            AI-assisted development workflows that changed where a small
            team's actual bottleneck sat.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>What I'm looking for</h2>
        <p>
          A mid-level engineering role, Melbourne hybrid or remote, available
          now. Most of what I've shipped has been full stack, web and mobile,
          but I'm equally comfortable owning a backend system or a front-end
          build on its own. The range just means I can plug in wherever a
          team needs me.
        </p>
      </div>

      {
        SHOW_RESUME && (
          <a
            href={CONTACT.resumeHref}
            class="mt-10 inline-block rounded bg-signal px-5 py-3 font-mono text-sm text-ink transition-opacity hover:opacity-90"
          >
            Download résumé (PDF)
          </a>
        )
      }
    </div>
  </article>

  <div class="border-t border-panel-line">
    <ContactSection />
  </div>
</Layout>
